Content:
Paths of Glory is a novel by English author Jeffrey Archer based on the story of George Mallory. It was published by St. Martin's Press on 3 March 2009. It claims that George Mallory, an Englishman, was the first to conquer Mount Everest  before Sir Edmund Hillary. The novel caused a controversy in New Zealand, with major newspaper the Dominion Post calling it an insult to Sir Edmund Hillary.[1]
